Actually, when I bought my last car, I did almost EXACTLY that.  And you know what, after a bit of haggling, I got the car I was happy with, at a price I could live with, and they added the stuff I wanted.  Anyone who walks into a dealership and plunks down the price they quote right off of the bat is either got too much money or they are a fool.  I will never have too much money, and I'm not a fool (well, not usually).<br>
<br>
What I don't understand from your second paragraph, is if you don't trust price checks and you don't trust price sights, why would you trust an offer made to you, as reflecting the true value?  If I have to sell anything (which I despise doing) I check the price guides, consider what I know the games/server situation and adjust accordingly.  I know approximately what I want to give/get in any trade, and I work from there.<br>
<br>
Consider this:<br>
<br>
me auction: selling MoSS<br>
buyer: what are you looking for?<br>
me: about 3k<br>
buyer: will you take a trade?<br>
me: really only interested in plat<br>
buyer: will you take 2600p?<br>
me: Yes, I will<br>
<br>
What's so hard about that?  I had an approximate price, he knew what he could afford.  If I didn't want the 2600p, I could have just said, no, thanks.  <br>
