<p><center><b><font size=2 color="WHITE"> "Hello, welcome to Fat Cretin's Loft of Repulsion, may I interest you in a flabby white-trash shake?" </font></b></center></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukerryndarkwater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerryn Darkwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 358<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/2/01 3:41:09 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greedy Fucks</span><hr size=1> Cao, my point is that you and I both know you didn't use the words BASTARD...I can get a better car cheaper elsewhere. We both know that you politely said something along the lines of &quot;No..im not going to but it for that price because I've seen a better car cheaper elsewhere&quot; Which is fine. Why then do people feel that they can be less polite in EQ?<br>
<br>
I got my car down for £3600 to £3000, I also had them throw in a 1 yr warranty, 3 years servicing, a new set of tyres, a years tax and a CD player. Not to mention I had them replace the sun visors which were a bit manky, repair a cigarette burn in a seat and replace a broken speaker along with about 100 other minor things. All with the words &quot;Hmmn...thats a little bit more then I was hoping to pay&quot;<br>
<br>
So why do I trust an offer as opposed to a price check. Well first of all let me clarify that for 95% of my sales I have a set price in my mind. These are because these items are usually larger sales to me. e.g I knew my wurmslayer was worth 3k when I came to sell it...because I'd seen dozens for sale for that price in EC whenver I walked through. I knew the FBSS I was selling was worth 9k for the same reason. I knew that I wasn't going to waiver on that. If everyone else is selling their WS for 3k Im not letting mine go for 2600pp because there will be someone along in 5 minutes who will pay me the 3k.<br>
<br>
But the Ro bracers? Make an offer....if its anywhere near halfway decent you get the bracer. It's not that Im greedy. It's just that I dont see them sell that often so Im not aware of the price. I also know that no matter what its not going to sell for very much. So I really couldn't care less. Guy says 400pp and I think &quot;Yeah thats fair,..bang you got it.&quot; Guy says 800pp and I think nah...thats too much and ill tell them so. Guy says 120pp and I think &quot;No sorry..i was hoping for a bit more then that&quot; I usually dont carry on the conversation because if theyre offering me 120pp for a ro bracer theyre either taking the piss or theyre as clueless as I am. In your example you knew what the MOSS was worth. For like one in 20 sales ( and I rarely have stuff for sale ) I don't think it's worth all the hassle.<br>
<br>
I totally agree that there are some greedy fucks out there that want as much money as they can get, and I totally agree that some of these greedy fucks are going to abuse the person who makes an offer. But I totally disagree that anyone who uses the statement &quot;Make an offer&quot; is a greedy fuck.<br>
<br>
Let me play around with the english language a little for people who have a problem with the way the auction channel works.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Auction</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> n.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> public sale where articles are sold to the highest bidder - <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> v.t</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> sell by auction.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bid</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> offer of a price, esp. at an auction (p.t. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> bid</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pres.p <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> bidding</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ) make a bid (of) offer etc. <p><HTML><CENTER>
